IRS Announces One-Week Extension for Storm-Tossed Tax Preparers

-- B y   R i c h a r d   R u b i n
-- 
2011-09-01T21:24:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/irs-announces-one-week-extension-for-storm-tossed-tax-preparers.html
The  Internal Revenue Service 
announced it was extending by one week a Sept. 15 filing
deadline for taxpayers whose preparers were affected by
Hurricane Irene.  The extension, which mostly affects corporations,
partnerships and trusts filing final 2010 returns, is available
in cases where preparers faced evacuation orders or severe
weather warnings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Rubin in  Washington  at 
 rrubin12@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Silva at 
 msilva34@bloomberg.net  